After a hectic and high-octane election campaign, the capital goes to polls today. To ensure safe polling, at least 40,000 Delhi Police personnel, 19,000 home guards, and 190 companies of paramilitary forces have been deployed across the city â€” apart from checking drives, flying squads and patrolling on boats in the Yamuna.

